  "texts": [
    "Clearly, S 3 strongly refines the near wake regions where gradients of the target metric are high, while creating a coarse grid in regions with low TKE.",
    "Regions with uniformly high metric values are not excessively refined, e.g., at a distance of one to three diameters downstream of the cylinder.",
    "As expected, the new grid is roughly symmetric with respect to the horizontal dividing line through the cylinder.Small asymmetries may occur because of the limited accuracy of the sampled TKE and the empirically chosen number of leave cells marked for refinement in each iteration.",
    "S 3 is able to capture the TKE without a qualitative deterioration of its approximation, as shown in fig.",
    "(7c) shows a second x-z-slice at y/d = 8."
